<task id="installation-instructions-macosx" >
    <title>OS X Installation</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>Installation <indexterm>OS X installation</indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context>To install <ph keyref="product"/>, on OS X:</context>
        <steps>
            <step>
        <cmd>Download the OS X Installation package (<ph keyref="archiveInstallMac"/>).</cmd>
        <info>The Safari web browser should recognize and expand the compressed file. If it is not
          automatically expanded, you can expand it manually by double clicking it.</info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Validate the integrity of the downloaded file by <xref
            href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Md5sum" format="html" scope="external">checking it
            against the MD5 sum</xref> published on the download page.
          <?oxy_comment_start author="Mark" timestamp="20140730T172107-0400" comment="If Safari automatically expands the file, how do you MD5sum it?"?></cmd>
        <?oxy_comment_end?>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>In <uicontrol>Finder</uicontrol>, move the expanded folder to your
            <filepath>Applications</filepath> folder. </cmd>
        <stepresult><ph keyref="product"/> is now installed.</stepresult>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Start <ph keyref="product"/>, using one of the following  methods:</cmd>
        <choices id="choices_wz3_qnk_x4">
          <choice>
            <p>Double click Oxygen.app</p>
          </choice>
          <choice>Run <codeph product="editor">sh oxygenMac.sh</codeph><codeph product="author">sh
              oxygenAuthorMac.sh</codeph><codeph product="developer">sh
              oxygenDeveloperMac.sh</codeph><codeph product="svnClient">sh
              syncroSVNClientMac.sh</codeph> on the command line. </choice>
        </choices>
        <info>
          <note type="notice">You can start more than one instance on the same computer by running
            the following command for each new
            instance:<screen xml:space="preserve">open -n <ph keyref="executableMac"/></screen></note>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>To license your copy of <ph keyref="product"/>, go to <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Help</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Register...</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> to enter your <xref keyref="install.license-key">license key</xref>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <note>
            <p>To avoid an unpredictable behavior of the cursor, use a fixed-size font, for example
              Monaco. You can find more details about this behaviour <xref
                href="http://www.oxygenxml.com/forum/topic64.html" format="html" scope="external"
                >here</xref>.<?oxy_comment_start author="Mark" timestamp="20140730T172120-0400" comment="This issue was reported in 2003 and the last entry on the thread (which sounds like an isolated incident) was in 2009. Is this still an issue? If so, it belongs in troubleshooting, not here. "?></p>
            <?oxy_comment_end?>
          </note>
        </info>
      </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
